155// Class to automatically disable occlusion query upon entering block and re-able it upon
156// exiting block.
157struct ScopedDisableOcclusionQuery
158{
159 ScopedDisableOcclusionQuery(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
160 RenderCommandEncoder *encoder,
161 angle::Result *resultOut)
162 : mContextMtl(contextMtl), mEncoder(encoder), mResultOut(resultOut)
163 {
164#ifndef NDEBUG
165 if (contextMtl->hasActiveOcclusionQuery())
166 {
167 encoder->pushDebugGroup(@"Disabled OcclusionQuery");
168 }
169#endif
170 // temporarily disable occlusion query
171 contextMtl->disableActiveOcclusionQueryInRenderPass();
172 }
173 ~ScopedDisableOcclusionQuery()
174 {
175 *mResultOut = mContextMtl->restartActiveOcclusionQueryInRenderPass();
176#ifndef NDEBUG
177 if (mContextMtl->hasActiveOcclusionQuery())
178 {
179 mEncoder->popDebugGroup();
180 }
181#else
182 ANGLE_UNUSED_VARIABLE(mEncoder);
183#endif
184 }
185
186 private:
187 ContextMtl *mContextMtl;
188 RenderCommandEncoder *mEncoder;
189
190 angle::Result *mResultOut;
191};

193void GetBlitTexCoords(uint32_t srcWidth,
194 uint32_t srcHeight,
195 const gl::Rectangle &srcRect,
196 bool srcYFlipped,
197 bool unpackFlipX,
198 bool unpackFlipY,
199 float *u0,
200 float *v0,
201 float *u1,
202 float *v1)
203{
204 int x0 = srcRect.x0(); // left
205 int x1 = srcRect.x1(); // right
206 int y0 = srcRect.y0(); // lower
207 int y1 = srcRect.y1(); // upper
208 if (srcYFlipped)
209 {
210 // If source's Y has been flipped, such as default framebuffer, then adjust the real source
211 // rectangle.
212 y0 = srcHeight - y1;
213 y1 = y0 + srcRect.height;
214 std::swap(y0, y1);
215 }
216
217 if (unpackFlipX)
218 {
219 std::swap(x0, x1);
220 }
221
222 if (unpackFlipY)
223 {
224 std::swap(y0, y1);
225 }
226
227 *u0 = static_cast<float>(x0) / srcWidth;
228 *u1 = static_cast<float>(x1) / srcWidth;
229 *v0 = static_cast<float>(y0) / srcHeight;
230 *v1 = static_cast<float>(y1) / srcHeight;
231}

233template <typename T>
234angle::Result GenTriFanFromClientElements(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
235 GLsizei count,
236 bool primitiveRestartEnabled,
237 const T *indices,
238 const BufferRef &dstBuffer,
239 uint32_t dstOffset,
240 uint32_t *indicesGenerated)
241{
242 ASSERT(count > 2);
243 constexpr T kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex = std::numeric_limits<T>::max();
244 GLsizei dstTriangle = 0;
245 uint32_t *dstPtr = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t *>(dstBuffer->map(contextMtl) + dstOffset);
246 T triFirstIdx, srcPrevIdx;
247 memcpy(&triFirstIdx, indices, sizeof(triFirstIdx));
248 memcpy(&srcPrevIdx, indices + 1, sizeof(srcPrevIdx));
249
250 if (primitiveRestartEnabled)
251 {
252 GLsizei triFirstIdxLoc = 0;
253 while (triFirstIdx == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex)
254 {
255 ++triFirstIdxLoc;
256 memcpy(&triFirstIdx, indices + triFirstIdxLoc, sizeof(triFirstIdx));
257 }
258
259 for (GLsizei i = triFirstIdxLoc + 2; i < count; ++i)
260 {
261 uint32_t triIndices[3];
262 T srcIdx;
263 memcpy(&srcIdx, indices + i, sizeof(srcIdx));
264 bool completeTriangle = true;
265 if (srcPrevIdx == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex || srcIdx == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex)
266 {
267 // Incomplete triangle. Move to next triangle and set triFirstIndex
268 triFirstIdx = srcIdx;
269 triFirstIdxLoc = i;
270 completeTriangle = false;
271 }
272 else if (i < triFirstIdxLoc + 2)
273 {
274 // Incomplete triangle, move to next triangle
275 completeTriangle = false;
276 }
277 else
278 {
279 triIndices[0] = triFirstIdx;
280 triIndices[1] = srcPrevIdx;
281 triIndices[2] = srcIdx;
282 }
283 if (completeTriangle)
284 {
285 memcpy(dstPtr + 3 * dstTriangle, triIndices, sizeof(triIndices));
286 ++dstTriangle;
287 }
288 srcPrevIdx = srcIdx;
289 }
290 }
291 else
292 {
293 for (GLsizei i = 2; i < count; ++i)
294 {
295 T srcIdx;
296 memcpy(&srcIdx, indices + i, sizeof(srcIdx));
297
298 uint32_t triIndices[3];
299 triIndices[0] = triFirstIdx;
300 triIndices[1] = srcPrevIdx;
301 triIndices[2] = srcIdx;
302 srcPrevIdx = srcIdx;
303
304 memcpy(dstPtr + 3 * dstTriangle, triIndices, sizeof(triIndices));
305 ++dstTriangle;
306 }
307 }
308 if (indicesGenerated)
309 *indicesGenerated = dstTriangle * 3;
310 dstBuffer->unmap(contextMtl);
311
312 return angle::Result::Continue;
313}

315template <typename T>
316angle::Result GenPrimitiveRestartBuffer(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
317 GLsizei count,
318 GLsizei indicesPerPrimitive,
319 const T *indices,
320 const BufferRef &dstBuffer,
321 uint32_t dstOffset,
322 size_t *indicesGenerated)
323{
324 constexpr T kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex = std::numeric_limits<T>::max();
325 uint32_t *dstPtr = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t *>(dstBuffer->map(contextMtl) + dstOffset);
326 GLsizei readValueLoc = 0;
327 T readValue = 0;
328 uint32_t dstIdx = 0;
329 memcpy(&readValue, indices, sizeof(readValue));
330 while (readValue == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex)
331 {
332
333 ++readValueLoc;
334 memcpy(&readValue, indices + readValueLoc, sizeof(readValue));
335 }
336 while (readValueLoc + indicesPerPrimitive <= count)
337 {
338
339 uint32_t primIndicies[3];
340 bool foundPrimitive = true;
341 for (int k = 0; k < indicesPerPrimitive; ++k)
342 {
343 memcpy(&readValue, indices + readValueLoc, sizeof(readValue));
344 ++readValueLoc;
345 if (readValue == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex)
346 {
347 foundPrimitive = false;
348 break;
349 }
350 else
351 {
352 primIndicies[k] = (uint32_t)readValue;
353 }
354 }
355 if (foundPrimitive)
356 {
357 memcpy(&dstPtr[dstIdx], primIndicies, (indicesPerPrimitive) * sizeof(uint32_t));
358 dstIdx += indicesPerPrimitive;
359 }
360 }
361 if (indicesGenerated)
362 *indicesGenerated = dstIdx;
363 return angle::Result::Continue;
364}

366template <typename T>
367angle::Result GenLineLoopFromClientElements(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
368 GLsizei count,
369 bool primitiveRestartEnabled,
370 const T *indices,
371 const BufferRef &dstBuffer,
372 uint32_t dstOffset,
373 uint32_t *indicesGenerated)
374{
375 ASSERT(count >= 2);
376 constexpr T kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex = std::numeric_limits<T>::max();
377 const uint32_t kDstPrimitiveRestartIndex = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
378
379 uint32_t *dstPtr = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t *>(dstBuffer->map(contextMtl) + dstOffset);
380 T lineLoopFirstIdx;
381 memcpy(&lineLoopFirstIdx, indices, sizeof(lineLoopFirstIdx));
382
383 if (primitiveRestartEnabled)
384 {
385 GLsizei lineLoopFirstIdxLoc = 0;
386 while (lineLoopFirstIdx == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex)
387 {
388 memcpy(&dstPtr[lineLoopFirstIdxLoc++], &kDstPrimitiveRestartIndex,
389 sizeof(kDstPrimitiveRestartIndex));
390 memcpy(&lineLoopFirstIdx, indices + lineLoopFirstIdxLoc, sizeof(lineLoopFirstIdx));
391 }
392
393 uint32_t dstIdx = lineLoopFirstIdx;
394 memcpy(&dstPtr[lineLoopFirstIdxLoc], &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
395 uint32_t dstWritten = lineLoopFirstIdxLoc + 1;
396
397 for (GLsizei i = lineLoopFirstIdxLoc + 1; i < count; ++i)
398 {
399 T srcIdx;
400 memcpy(&srcIdx, indices + i, sizeof(srcIdx));
401 if (srcIdx == kSrcPrimitiveRestartIndex)
402 {
403 // breaking line strip
404 dstIdx = lineLoopFirstIdx;
405 memcpy(&dstPtr[dstWritten++], &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
406 memcpy(&dstPtr[dstWritten++], &kDstPrimitiveRestartIndex,
407 sizeof(kDstPrimitiveRestartIndex));
408 lineLoopFirstIdxLoc = i + 1;
409 }
410 else
411 {
412 dstIdx = srcIdx;
413 memcpy(&dstPtr[dstWritten++], &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
414 if (lineLoopFirstIdxLoc == i)
415 {
416 lineLoopFirstIdx = srcIdx;
417 }
418 }
419 }
420
421 if (lineLoopFirstIdxLoc < count)
422 {
423 // last segment
424 dstIdx = lineLoopFirstIdx;
425 memcpy(&dstPtr[dstWritten++], &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
426 }
427
428 *indicesGenerated = dstWritten;
429 }
430 else
431 {
432 uint32_t dstIdx = lineLoopFirstIdx;
433 memcpy(dstPtr, &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
434 memcpy(dstPtr + count, &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
435 for (GLsizei i = 1; i < count; ++i)
436 {
437 T srcIdx;
438 memcpy(&srcIdx, indices + i, sizeof(srcIdx));
439
440 dstIdx = srcIdx;
441 memcpy(dstPtr + i, &dstIdx, sizeof(dstIdx));
442 }
443
444 *indicesGenerated = count + 1;
445 }
446 dstBuffer->unmap(contextMtl);
447
448 return angle::Result::Continue;
449}

451template <typename T>
452void GetFirstLastIndicesFromClientElements(GLsizei count,
453 const T *indices,
454 uint32_t *firstOut,
455 uint32_t *lastOut)
456{
457 *firstOut = 0;
458 *lastOut = 0;
459 memcpy(firstOut, indices, sizeof(indices[0]));
460 memcpy(lastOut, indices + count - 1, sizeof(indices[0]));
461}

463int GetShaderTextureType(const TextureRef &texture)
464{
465 if (!texture)
466 {
467 return -1;
468 }
469 switch (texture->textureType())
470 {
471 case MTLTextureType2D:
472 return mtl_shader::kTextureType2D;
473 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
474 return mtl_shader::kTextureType2DArray;
475 case MTLTextureType2DMultisample:
476 return mtl_shader::kTextureType2DMultisample;
477 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
478 return mtl_shader::kTextureTypeCube;
479 case MTLTextureType3D:
480 return mtl_shader::kTextureType3D;
481 default:
482 UNREACHABLE();
483 }
484
485 return 0;
486}
487
488int GetPixelTypeIndex(const angle::Format &angleFormat)
489{
490 if (angleFormat.isSint())
491 {
492 return static_cast<int>(PixelType::Int);
493 }
494 else if (angleFormat.isUint())
495 {
496 return static_cast<int>(PixelType::UInt);
497 }
498 else
499 {
500 return static_cast<int>(PixelType::Float);
501 }
502}

504ANGLE_INLINE
505void EnsureComputePipelineInitialized(DisplayMtl *display,
506 NSString *functionName,
507 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> *pipelineOut)
508{
509 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> &pipeline = *pipelineOut;
510 if (pipeline)
511 {
512 return;
513 }
514
515 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
516 {
517 id<MTLDevice> metalDevice = display->getMetalDevice();
518 auto shaderLib = display->getDefaultShadersLib();
519 NSError *err = nil;
520 id<MTLFunction> shader = [shaderLib newFunctionWithName:functionName];
521
522 [shader ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
523
524 pipeline = [[metalDevice newComputePipelineStateWithFunction:shader
525 error:&err] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
526 if (err && !pipeline)
527 {
528 ERR() << "Internal error: " << err.localizedDescription.UTF8String << "\n";
529 }
530
531 ASSERT(pipeline);
532 }
533}
534
535ANGLE_INLINE
536void EnsureSpecializedComputePipelineInitialized(
537 DisplayMtl *display,
538 NSString *functionName,
539 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants,
540 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> *pipelineOut)
541{
542 if (!funcConstants)
543 {
544 // Non specialized constants provided, use default creation function.
545 EnsureComputePipelineInitialized(display, functionName, pipelineOut);
546 return;
547 }
548
549 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> &pipeline = *pipelineOut;
550 if (pipeline)
551 {
552 return;
553 }
554
555 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
556 {
557 id<MTLDevice> metalDevice = display->getMetalDevice();
558 auto shaderLib = display->getDefaultShadersLib();
559 NSError *err = nil;
560
561 id<MTLFunction> shader = [shaderLib newFunctionWithName:functionName
562 constantValues:funcConstants
563 error:&err];
564 if (err && !shader)
565 {
566 ERR() << "Internal error: " << err.localizedDescription.UTF8String << "\n";
567 }
568 ASSERT([shader ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE]);
569
570 pipeline = [[metalDevice newComputePipelineStateWithFunction:shader
571 error:&err] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
572 if (err && !pipeline)
573 {
574 ERR() << "Internal error: " << err.localizedDescription.UTF8String << "\n";
575 }
576 ASSERT(pipeline);
577 }
578}

580// Function to initialize render pipeline cache with only vertex shader.
581ANGLE_INLINE
582void EnsureVertexShaderOnlyPipelineCacheInitialized(Context *context,
583 NSString *vertexFunctionName,
584 id<MTLLibrary> shaderLib,
585 RenderPipelineCache *pipelineCacheOut)
586{
587 RenderPipelineCache &pipelineCache = *pipelineCacheOut;
588 if (pipelineCache.getVertexShader())
589 {
590 // Already initialized
591 return;
592 }
593
594 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
595 {
596 id<MTLFunction> shader = [shaderLib newFunctionWithName:vertexFunctionName];
597
598 ASSERT([shader ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE]);
599
600 pipelineCache.setVertexShader(context, shader);
601 }
602}

604// Function to initialize specialized render pipeline cache with only vertex shader.
605ANGLE_INLINE
606void EnsureSpecializedVertexShaderOnlyPipelineCacheInitialized(
607 Context *context,
608 NSString *vertexFunctionName,
609 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants,
610 RenderPipelineCache *pipelineCacheOut)
611{
612 if (!funcConstants)
613 {
614 // Non specialized constants provided, use default creation function.
615 DisplayMtl *display = context->getDisplay();
616 auto shaderLib = display->getDefaultShadersLib();
617 EnsureVertexShaderOnlyPipelineCacheInitialized(context, vertexFunctionName, shaderLib,
618 pipelineCacheOut);
619 return;
620 }
621
622 RenderPipelineCache &pipelineCache = *pipelineCacheOut;
623 if (pipelineCache.getVertexShader())
624 {
625 // Already initialized
626 return;
627 }
628
629 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
630 {
631 DisplayMtl *display = context->getDisplay();
632 auto shaderLib = display->getDefaultShadersLib();
633 NSError *err = nil;
634
635 id<MTLFunction> shader = [shaderLib newFunctionWithName:vertexFunctionName
636 constantValues:funcConstants
637 error:&err];
638 if (err && !shader)
639 {
640 ERR() << "Internal error: " << err.localizedDescription.UTF8String << "\n";
641 }
642 ASSERT([shader ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE]);
643
644 pipelineCache.setVertexShader(context, shader);
645 }
646}

648// Get pipeline descriptor for render pipeline that contains vertex shader acting as compute shader.
649ANGLE_INLINE
650RenderPipelineDesc GetComputingVertexShaderOnlyRenderPipelineDesc(RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder)
651{
652 RenderPipelineDesc pipelineDesc;
653 const RenderPassDesc &renderPassDesc = cmdEncoder->renderPassDesc();
654
655 renderPassDesc.populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(&pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor);
656 pipelineDesc.rasterizationType = RenderPipelineRasterization::Disabled;
657 pipelineDesc.inputPrimitiveTopology = kPrimitiveTopologyClassPoint;
658
659 return pipelineDesc;
660}

714// Dispatch compute using 3D grid
715void DispatchCompute(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
716 ComputeCommandEncoder *encoder,
717 bool allowNonUniform,
718 const MTLSize &numThreads,
719 const MTLSize &threadsPerThreadgroup)
720{
721 if (allowNonUniform && contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasNonUniformDispatch.enabled)
722 {
723 encoder->dispatchNonUniform(numThreads, threadsPerThreadgroup);
724 }
725 else
726 {
727 MTLSize groups = MTLSizeMake(
728 (numThreads.width + threadsPerThreadgroup.width - 1) / threadsPerThreadgroup.width,
729 (numThreads.height + threadsPerThreadgroup.height - 1) / threadsPerThreadgroup.height,
730 (numThreads.depth + threadsPerThreadgroup.depth - 1) / threadsPerThreadgroup.depth);
731 encoder->dispatch(groups, threadsPerThreadgroup);
732 }
733}
734
735// Dispatch compute using 1D grid
736void DispatchCompute(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
737 ComputeCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
738 id<MTLComputePipelineState> pipelineState,
739 size_t numThreads)
740{
741 NSUInteger w = std::min<NSUInteger>(pipelineState.threadExecutionWidth, numThreads);
742 MTLSize threadsPerThreadgroup = MTLSizeMake(w, 1, 1);
743
744 if (contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasNonUniformDispatch.enabled)
745 {
746 MTLSize threads = MTLSizeMake(numThreads, 1, 1);
747 cmdEncoder->dispatchNonUniform(threads, threadsPerThreadgroup);
748 }
749 else
750 {
751 MTLSize groups = MTLSizeMake((numThreads + w - 1) / w, 1, 1);
752 cmdEncoder->dispatch(groups, threadsPerThreadgroup);
753 }
754}

763void SetupBlitWithDrawUniformData(RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
764 const BlitParams &params,
765 bool isColorBlit)
766{
767
768 BlitParamsUniform uniformParams;
769 uniformParams.dstFlipX = params.dstFlipX ? 1 : 0;
770 uniformParams.dstFlipY = params.dstFlipY ? 1 : 0;
771 uniformParams.srcLevel = params.srcLevel.get();
772 uniformParams.srcLayer = params.srcLayer;
773 if (isColorBlit)
774 {
775 const ColorBlitParams *colorParams = static_cast<const ColorBlitParams *>(&params);
776 uniformParams.dstLuminance = colorParams->dstLuminance ? 1 : 0;
777 }
778
779 // Compute source texCoords
780 uint32_t srcWidth = 0, srcHeight = 0;
781 if (params.src)
782 {
783 srcWidth = params.src->width(params.srcLevel);
784 srcHeight = params.src->height(params.srcLevel);
785 }
786 else if (!isColorBlit)
787 {
788 const DepthStencilBlitParams *dsParams =
789 static_cast<const DepthStencilBlitParams *>(&params);
790 srcWidth = dsParams->srcStencil->width(dsParams->srcLevel);
791 srcHeight = dsParams->srcStencil->height(dsParams->srcLevel);
792 }
793 else
794 {
795 UNREACHABLE();
796 }
797
798 float u0, v0, u1, v1;
799 GetBlitTexCoords(srcWidth, srcHeight, params.srcRect, params.srcYFlipped, params.unpackFlipX,
800 params.unpackFlipY, &u0, &v0, &u1, &v1);
801
802 float du = u1 - u0;
803 float dv = v1 - v0;
804
805 // lower left
806 uniformParams.srcTexCoords[0][0] = u0;
807 uniformParams.srcTexCoords[0][1] = v0;
808
809 // lower right
810 uniformParams.srcTexCoords[1][0] = u1 + du;
811 uniformParams.srcTexCoords[1][1] = v0;
812
813 // upper left
814 uniformParams.srcTexCoords[2][0] = u0;
815 uniformParams.srcTexCoords[2][1] = v1 + dv;
816
817 cmdEncoder->setVertexData(uniformParams, 0);
818 cmdEncoder->setFragmentData(uniformParams, 0);
819}
820
821void SetupCommonBlitWithDrawStates(const gl::Context *context,
822 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
823 const BlitParams &params,
824 bool isColorBlit)
825{
826 // Setup states
827 SetupFullscreenQuadDrawCommonStates(cmdEncoder);
828
829 // Viewport
830 MTLViewport viewportMtl =
831 GetViewport(params.dstRect, params.dstTextureSize.height, params.dstFlipY);
832 MTLScissorRect scissorRectMtl =
833 GetScissorRect(params.dstScissorRect, params.dstTextureSize.height, params.dstFlipY);
834 cmdEncoder->setViewport(viewportMtl);
835 cmdEncoder->setScissorRect(scissorRectMtl);
836
837 if (params.src)
838 {
839 cmdEncoder->setFragmentTexture(params.src, 0);
840 }
841
842 // Uniform
843 SetupBlitWithDrawUniformData(cmdEncoder, params, isColorBlit);
844}

1234
1235void ClearUtils::ensureRenderPipelineStateCacheInitialized(ContextMtl *ctx, uint32_t numOutputs)
1236{
1237 RenderPipelineCache &cache = mClearRenderPipelineCache[numOutputs];
1238 if (cache.getVertexShader() && cache.getFragmentShader())
1239 {
1240 // Already initialized.
1241 return;
1242 }
1243
1244 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1245 {
1246 NSError *err = nil;
1247 id<MTLLibrary> shaderLib = ctx->getDisplay()->getDefaultShadersLib();
1248 id<MTLFunction> vertexShader =
1249 [[shaderLib newFunctionWithName:@"clearVS"] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1250 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants =
1251 [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1252
1253 // Create clear shader pipeline cache for each number of color outputs.
1254 // So clear k color outputs will use mClearRenderPipelineCache[k] for example:
1255 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&numOutputs
1256 type:MTLDataTypeUInt
1257 withName:NUM_COLOR_OUTPUTS_CONSTANT_NAME];
1258
1259 id<MTLFunction> fragmentShader = [[shaderLib
1260 newFunctionWithName:[NSString stringWithUTF8String:mFragmentShaderName.c_str()]
1261 constantValues:funcConstants
1262 error:&err] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1263 ASSERT(fragmentShader);
1264
1265 cache.setVertexShader(ctx, vertexShader);
1266 cache.setFragmentShader(ctx, fragmentShader);
1267 }
1268}
1269
1270id<MTLDepthStencilState> ClearUtils::getClearDepthStencilState(const gl::Context *context,
1271 const ClearRectParams &params)
1272{
1273 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1274
1275 if (!params.clearDepth.valid() && !params.clearStencil.valid())
1276 {
1277 // Doesn't clear depth nor stencil
1278 return contextMtl->getDisplay()->getStateCache().getNullDepthStencilState(contextMtl);
1279 }
1280
1281 DepthStencilDesc desc;
1282 desc.reset();
1283
1284 if (params.clearDepth.valid())
1285 {
1286 // Clear depth state
1287 desc.depthWriteEnabled = true;
1288 }
1289 else
1290 {
1291 desc.depthWriteEnabled = false;
1292 }
1293
1294 if (params.clearStencil.valid())
1295 {
1296 // Clear stencil state
1297 desc.frontFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = MTLStencilOperationReplace;
1298 desc.frontFaceStencil.writeMask = contextMtl->getStencilMask();
1299 desc.backFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = MTLStencilOperationReplace;
1300 desc.backFaceStencil.writeMask = contextMtl->getStencilMask();
1301 }
1302
1303 return contextMtl->getDisplay()->getStateCache().getDepthStencilState(
1304 contextMtl->getMetalDevice(), desc);
1305}
1306
1307id<MTLRenderPipelineState> ClearUtils::getClearRenderPipelineState(const gl::Context *context,
1308 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1309 const ClearRectParams &params)
1310{
1311 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1312 // The color mask to be applied to every color attachment:
1313 MTLColorWriteMask globalColorMask = params.clearColorMask;
1314 if (!params.clearColor.valid())
1315 {
1316 globalColorMask = MTLColorWriteMaskNone;
1317 }
1318
1319 RenderPipelineDesc pipelineDesc;
1320 const RenderPassDesc &renderPassDesc = cmdEncoder->renderPassDesc();
1321
1322 renderPassDesc.populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(globalColorMask,
1323 &pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor);
1324
1325 // Disable clear for some outputs that are not enabled
1326 pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor.updateEnabledDrawBuffers(params.enabledBuffers);
1327
1328 pipelineDesc.inputPrimitiveTopology = kPrimitiveTopologyClassTriangle;
1329
1330 ensureRenderPipelineStateCacheInitialized(contextMtl, renderPassDesc.numColorAttachments);
1331 RenderPipelineCache &cache = mClearRenderPipelineCache[renderPassDesc.numColorAttachments];
1332
1333 return cache.getRenderPipelineState(contextMtl, pipelineDesc);
1334}
1335
1336angle::Result ClearUtils::setupClearWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
1337 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1338 const ClearRectParams &params)
1339{
1340 // Generate render pipeline state
1341 id<MTLRenderPipelineState> renderPipelineState =
1342 getClearRenderPipelineState(context, cmdEncoder, params);
1343 if(renderPipelineState == nil)
1344 {
1345 //Return early
1346 return angle::Result::Stop;
1347 }
1348 ASSERT(renderPipelineState);
1349 // Setup states
1350 SetupFullscreenQuadDrawCommonStates(cmdEncoder);
1351 cmdEncoder->setRenderPipelineState(renderPipelineState);
1352
1353 id<MTLDepthStencilState> dsState = getClearDepthStencilState(context, params);
1354 cmdEncoder->setDepthStencilState(dsState).setStencilRefVal(params.clearStencil.value());
1355
1356 // Viewports
1357 MTLViewport viewport;
1358 MTLScissorRect scissorRect;
1359
1360 viewport = GetViewport(params.clearArea, params.dstTextureSize.height, params.flipY);
1361
1362 scissorRect = GetScissorRect(params.clearArea, params.dstTextureSize.height, params.flipY);
1363
1364 cmdEncoder->setViewport(viewport);
1365 cmdEncoder->setScissorRect(scissorRect);
1366
1367 // uniform
1368 ClearParamsUniform uniformParams;
1369 const ClearColorValue &clearValue = params.clearColor.value();
1370 // ClearColorValue is an int, uint, float union so it's safe to use only floats.
1371 // The Shader will do the bit cast based on appropriate format type.
1372 // See shaders/clear.metal (3 variants ClearFloatFS, ClearIntFS and ClearUIntFS each does the
1373 // appropriate bit cast)
1374 ASSERT(sizeof(uniformParams.clearColor) == clearValue.getValueBytes().size());
1375 std::memcpy(uniformParams.clearColor, clearValue.getValueBytes().data(),
1376 clearValue.getValueBytes().size());
1377 uniformParams.clearDepth = params.clearDepth.value();
1378
1379 cmdEncoder->setVertexData(uniformParams, 0);
1380 cmdEncoder->setFragmentData(uniformParams, 0);
1381 return angle::Result::Continue;
1382}
1383
1384angle::Result ClearUtils::clearWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
1385 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1386 const ClearRectParams &params)
1387{
1388 ClearRectParams overridedParams = params;
1389 // Make sure we don't clear attachment that doesn't exist
1390 const RenderPassDesc &renderPassDesc = cmdEncoder->renderPassDesc();
1391 if (renderPassDesc.numColorAttachments == 0)
1392 {
1393 overridedParams.clearColor.reset();
1394 }
1395 if (!renderPassDesc.depthAttachment.texture())
1396 {
1397 overridedParams.clearDepth.reset();
1398 }
1399 if (!renderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.texture())
1400 {
1401 overridedParams.clearStencil.reset();
1402 }
1403
1404 if (!overridedParams.clearColor.valid() && !overridedParams.clearDepth.valid() &&
1405 !overridedParams.clearStencil.valid())
1406 {
1407 return angle::Result::Continue;
1408 }
1409 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1410 ANGLE_TRY(setupClearWithDraw(context, cmdEncoder, overridedParams));
1411
1412 angle::Result result;
1413 {
1414 // Need to disable occlusion query, otherwise clearing will affect the occlusion counting
1415 ScopedDisableOcclusionQuery disableOcclusionQuery(contextMtl, cmdEncoder, &result);
1416 // Draw the screen aligned triangle
1417 cmdEncoder->draw(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, 0, 3);
1418 }
1419
1420 // Invalidate current context's state
1421 contextMtl->invalidateState(context);
1422
1423 return result;
1424}

1440
1441void ColorBlitUtils::ensureRenderPipelineStateCacheInitialized(ContextMtl *ctx,
1442 uint32_t numOutputs,
1443 int alphaPremultiplyType,
1444 int textureType,
1445 RenderPipelineCache *cacheOut)
1446{
1447 RenderPipelineCache &pipelineCache = *cacheOut;
1448 if (pipelineCache.getVertexShader() && pipelineCache.getFragmentShader())
1449 {
1450 // Already initialized.
1451 return;
1452 }
1453
1454 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1455 {
1456 NSError *err = nil;
1457 id<MTLLibrary> shaderLib = ctx->getDisplay()->getDefaultShadersLib();
1458 id<MTLFunction> vertexShader =
1459 [[shaderLib newFunctionWithName:@"blitVS"] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1460 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants =
1461 [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1462
1463 constexpr BOOL multiplyAlphaFlags[][2] = {// premultiply, unmultiply
1464
1465 // Normal blit
1466 {NO, NO},
1467 // Blit premultiply-alpha
1468 {YES, NO},
1469 // Blit unmultiply alpha
1470 {NO, YES}};
1471
1472 // Set alpha multiply flags
1473 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&multiplyAlphaFlags[alphaPremultiplyType][0]
1474 type:MTLDataTypeBool
1475 withName:PREMULTIPLY_ALPHA_CONSTANT_NAME];
1476 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&multiplyAlphaFlags[alphaPremultiplyType][1]
1477 type:MTLDataTypeBool
1478 withName:UNMULTIPLY_ALPHA_CONSTANT_NAME];
1479
1480 // We create blit shader pipeline cache for each number of color outputs.
1481 // So blit k color outputs will use mBlitRenderPipelineCache[k-1] for example:
1482 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&numOutputs
1483 type:MTLDataTypeUInt
1484 withName:NUM_COLOR_OUTPUTS_CONSTANT_NAME];
1485
1486 // Set texture type constant
1487 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&textureType
1488 type:MTLDataTypeInt
1489 withName:SOURCE_TEXTURE_TYPE_CONSTANT_NAME];
1490
1491 id<MTLFunction> fragmentShader = [[shaderLib
1492 newFunctionWithName:[NSString stringWithUTF8String:mFragmentShaderName.c_str()]
1493 constantValues:funcConstants
1494 error:&err] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1495
1496 ASSERT(vertexShader);
1497 ASSERT(fragmentShader);
1498 pipelineCache.setVertexShader(ctx, vertexShader);
1499 pipelineCache.setFragmentShader(ctx, fragmentShader);
1500 }
1501}
1502
1503id<MTLRenderPipelineState> ColorBlitUtils::getColorBlitRenderPipelineState(
1504 const gl::Context *context,
1505 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1506 const ColorBlitParams &params)
1507{
1508 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1509 RenderPipelineDesc pipelineDesc;
1510 const RenderPassDesc &renderPassDesc = cmdEncoder->renderPassDesc();
1511
1512 renderPassDesc.populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(params.blitColorMask,
1513 &pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor);
1514
1515 // Disable blit for some outputs that are not enabled
1516 pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor.updateEnabledDrawBuffers(params.enabledBuffers);
1517
1518 pipelineDesc.inputPrimitiveTopology = kPrimitiveTopologyClassTriangle;
1519
1520 RenderPipelineCache *pipelineCache;
1521 int alphaPremultiplyType;
1522 uint32_t nOutputIndex = renderPassDesc.numColorAttachments - 1;
1523 int textureType = GetShaderTextureType(params.src);
1524 if (params.unpackPremultiplyAlpha == params.unpackUnmultiplyAlpha)
1525 {
1526 alphaPremultiplyType = 0;
1527 pipelineCache = &mBlitRenderPipelineCache[nOutputIndex][textureType];
1528 }
1529 else if (params.unpackPremultiplyAlpha)
1530 {
1531 alphaPremultiplyType = 1;
1532 pipelineCache = &mBlitPremultiplyAlphaRenderPipelineCache[nOutputIndex][textureType];
1533 }
1534 else
1535 {
1536 alphaPremultiplyType = 2;
1537 pipelineCache = &mBlitUnmultiplyAlphaRenderPipelineCache[nOutputIndex][textureType];
1538 }
1539
1540 ensureRenderPipelineStateCacheInitialized(contextMtl, renderPassDesc.numColorAttachments,
1541 alphaPremultiplyType, textureType, pipelineCache);
1542
1543 return pipelineCache->getRenderPipelineState(contextMtl, pipelineDesc);
1544}

1546angle::Result ColorBlitUtils::setupColorBlitWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
1547 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1548 const ColorBlitParams &params)
1549{
1550 ASSERT(cmdEncoder->renderPassDesc().numColorAttachments >= 1 && params.src);
1551
1552 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1553
1554 // Generate render pipeline state
1555 id<MTLRenderPipelineState> renderPipelineState =
1556 getColorBlitRenderPipelineState(context, cmdEncoder, params);
1557 ASSERT(renderPipelineState);
1558 if(!renderPipelineState)
1559 {
1560 //return early
1561 return angle::Result::Stop;
1562 }
1563 // Setup states
1564 cmdEncoder->setRenderPipelineState(renderPipelineState);
1565 cmdEncoder->setDepthStencilState(
1566 contextMtl->getDisplay()->getStateCache().getNullDepthStencilState(contextMtl));
1567
1568 SetupCommonBlitWithDrawStates(context, cmdEncoder, params, true);
1569
1570 // Set sampler state
1571 SamplerDesc samplerDesc;
1572 samplerDesc.reset();
1573 samplerDesc.minFilter = samplerDesc.magFilter = GetFilter(params.filter);
1574
1575 cmdEncoder->setFragmentSamplerState(contextMtl->getDisplay()->getStateCache().getSamplerState(
1576 contextMtl->getMetalDevice(), samplerDesc),
1577 0, FLT_MAX, 0);
1578 return angle::Result::Continue;
1579}

1581angle::Result ColorBlitUtils::blitColorWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
1582 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1583 const ColorBlitParams &params)
1584{
1585 if (!params.src)
1586 {
1587 return angle::Result::Continue;
1588 }
1589 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1590 ANGLE_TRY(setupColorBlitWithDraw(context, cmdEncoder, params));
1591
1592 angle::Result result;
1593 {
1594 // Need to disable occlusion query, otherwise blitting will affect the occlusion counting
1595 ScopedDisableOcclusionQuery disableOcclusionQuery(contextMtl, cmdEncoder, &result);
1596 // Draw the screen aligned triangle
1597 cmdEncoder->draw(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, 0, 3);
1598 }
1599
1600 // Invalidate current context's state
1601 contextMtl->invalidateState(context);
1602
1603 return result;
1604}

1618void DepthStencilBlitUtils::ensureRenderPipelineStateCacheInitialized(ContextMtl *ctx,
1619 int sourceDepthTextureType,
1620 int sourceStencilTextureType,
1621 RenderPipelineCache *cacheOut)
1622{
1623 RenderPipelineCache &cache = *cacheOut;
1624 if (cache.getVertexShader() && cache.getFragmentShader())
1625 {
1626 // Already initialized.
1627 return;
1628 }
1629
1630 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1631 {
1632 NSError *err = nil;
1633 id<MTLLibrary> shaderLib = ctx->getDisplay()->getDefaultShadersLib();
1634 id<MTLFunction> vertexShader =
1635 [[shaderLib newFunctionWithName:@"blitVS"] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1636 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants =
1637 [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1638
1639 NSString *shaderName;
1640 if (sourceDepthTextureType != -1 && sourceStencilTextureType != -1)
1641 {
1642 shaderName = @"blitDepthStencilFS";
1643 }
1644 else if (sourceDepthTextureType != -1)
1645 {
1646 shaderName = @"blitDepthFS";
1647 }
1648 else
1649 {
1650 shaderName = @"blitStencilFS";
1651 }
1652
1653 if (sourceDepthTextureType != -1)
1654 {
1655 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&sourceDepthTextureType
1656 type:MTLDataTypeInt
1657 withName:SOURCE_TEXTURE_TYPE_CONSTANT_NAME];
1658 }
1659 if (sourceStencilTextureType != -1)
1660 {
1661
1662 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&sourceStencilTextureType
1663 type:MTLDataTypeInt
1664 withName:SOURCE_TEXTURE2_TYPE_CONSTANT_NAME];
1665 }
1666
1667 id<MTLFunction> fragmentShader =
1668 [[shaderLib newFunctionWithName:shaderName constantValues:funcConstants
1669 error:&err] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1670 ASSERT(fragmentShader);
1671
1672 cache.setVertexShader(ctx, vertexShader);
1673 cache.setFragmentShader(ctx, fragmentShader);
1674 }
1675}

1704id<MTLRenderPipelineState> DepthStencilBlitUtils::getDepthStencilBlitRenderPipelineState(
1705 const gl::Context *context,
1706 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1707 const DepthStencilBlitParams &params)
1708{
1709 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1710 RenderPipelineDesc pipelineDesc;
1711 const RenderPassDesc &renderPassDesc = cmdEncoder->renderPassDesc();
1712
1713 renderPassDesc.populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(&pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor);
1714
1715 // Disable all color outputs
1716 pipelineDesc.outputDescriptor.updateEnabledDrawBuffers(gl::DrawBufferMask());
1717
1718 pipelineDesc.inputPrimitiveTopology = kPrimitiveTopologyClassTriangle;
1719
1720 RenderPipelineCache *pipelineCache;
1721
1722 int depthTextureType = GetShaderTextureType(params.src);
1723 int stencilTextureType = GetShaderTextureType(params.srcStencil);
1724 if (params.src && params.srcStencil)
1725 {
1726 pipelineCache = &mDepthStencilBlitRenderPipelineCache[depthTextureType][stencilTextureType];
1727 }
1728 else if (params.src)
1729 {
1730 // Only depth blit
1731 pipelineCache = &mDepthBlitRenderPipelineCache[depthTextureType];
1732 }
1733 else
1734 {
1735 // Only stencil blit
1736 pipelineCache = &mStencilBlitRenderPipelineCache[stencilTextureType];
1737 }
1738
1739 ensureRenderPipelineStateCacheInitialized(contextMtl, depthTextureType, stencilTextureType,
1740 pipelineCache);
1741
1742 return pipelineCache->getRenderPipelineState(contextMtl, pipelineDesc);
1743}
1744
1745angle::Result DepthStencilBlitUtils::setupDepthStencilBlitWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
1746 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1747 const DepthStencilBlitParams &params)
1748{
1749 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
1750
1751 ASSERT(params.src || params.srcStencil);
1752
1753 SetupCommonBlitWithDrawStates(context, cmdEncoder, params, false);
1754
1755 // Generate render pipeline state
1756 id<MTLRenderPipelineState> renderPipelineState =
1757 getDepthStencilBlitRenderPipelineState(context, cmdEncoder, params);
1758 if(!renderPipelineState)
1759 {
1760 return angle::Result::Stop;
1761 }
1762 ASSERT(renderPipelineState);
1763 // Setup states
1764 cmdEncoder->setRenderPipelineState(renderPipelineState);
1765
1766 // Depth stencil state
1767 mtl::DepthStencilDesc dsStateDesc;
1768 dsStateDesc.reset();
1769 dsStateDesc.depthCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
1770
1771 if (params.src)
1772 {
1773 // Enable depth write
1774 dsStateDesc.depthWriteEnabled = true;
1775 }
1776 else
1777 {
1778 // Disable depth write
1779 dsStateDesc.depthWriteEnabled = false;
1780 }
1781
1782 if (params.srcStencil)
1783 {
1784 cmdEncoder->setFragmentTexture(params.srcStencil, 1);
1785
1786 if (!contextMtl->getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasStencilOutput.enabled)
1787 {
1788 // Hardware must support stencil writing directly in shader.
1789 UNREACHABLE();
1790 }
1791 // Enable stencil write to framebuffer
1792 dsStateDesc.frontFaceStencil.stencilCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
1793 dsStateDesc.backFaceStencil.stencilCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
1794
1795 dsStateDesc.frontFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = MTLStencilOperationReplace;
1796 dsStateDesc.backFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = MTLStencilOperationReplace;
1797
1798 dsStateDesc.frontFaceStencil.writeMask = kStencilMaskAll;
1799 dsStateDesc.backFaceStencil.writeMask = kStencilMaskAll;
1800 }
1801
1802 cmdEncoder->setDepthStencilState(contextMtl->getDisplay()->getStateCache().getDepthStencilState(
1803 contextMtl->getMetalDevice(), dsStateDesc));
1804 return angle::Result::Continue;
1805}

1807angle::Result DepthStencilBlitUtils::blitDepthStencilWithDraw(const gl::Context *context,
1808 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
1809 const DepthStencilBlitParams &params)
1810{
1811 if (!params.src && !params.srcStencil)
1812 {
1813 return angle::Result::Continue;
1814 }
1815 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1816
1817 ANGLE_TRY(setupDepthStencilBlitWithDraw(context, cmdEncoder, params));
1818
1819 angle::Result result;
1820 {
1821 // Need to disable occlusion query, otherwise blitting will affect the occlusion counting
1822 ScopedDisableOcclusionQuery disableOcclusionQuery(contextMtl, cmdEncoder, &result);
1823 // Draw the screen aligned triangle
1824 cmdEncoder->draw(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, 0, 3);
1825 }
1826
1827 // Invalidate current context's state
1828 contextMtl->invalidateState(context);
1829
1830 return result;
1831}
1832
1833angle::Result DepthStencilBlitUtils::blitStencilViaCopyBuffer(
1834 const gl::Context *context,
1835 const StencilBlitViaBufferParams &params)
1836{
1837 // Depth texture must be omitted.
1838 ASSERT(!params.src);
1839 if (!params.srcStencil || !params.dstStencil)
1840 {
1841 return angle::Result::Continue;
1842 }
1843 ContextMtl *contextMtl = GetImpl(context);
1844
1845 // Create intermediate buffer.
1846 uint32_t bufferRequiredRowPitch =
1847 static_cast<uint32_t>(params.dstRect.width) * params.dstStencil->samples();
1848 uint32_t bufferRequiredSize =
1849 bufferRequiredRowPitch * static_cast<uint32_t>(params.dstRect.height);
1850 if (!mStencilCopyBuffer || mStencilCopyBuffer->size() < bufferRequiredSize)
1851 {
1852 ANGLE_TRY(Buffer::MakeBuffer(contextMtl, bufferRequiredSize, nullptr, &mStencilCopyBuffer));
1853 }
1854
1855 // Copy stencil data to buffer via compute shader. We cannot use blit command since blit command
1856 // doesn't support multisample resolve and scaling.
1857 ComputeCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder = contextMtl->getComputeCommandEncoder();
1858 ASSERT(cmdEncoder);
1859
1860 id<MTLComputePipelineState> pipeline =
1861 getStencilToBufferComputePipelineState(contextMtl, params);
1862
1863 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(pipeline);
1864
1865 uint32_t srcWidth = params.srcStencil->width(params.srcLevel);
1866 uint32_t srcHeight = params.srcStencil->height(params.srcLevel);
1867
1868 float u0, v0, u1, v1;
1869 bool unpackFlipX = params.unpackFlipX;
1870 bool unpackFlipY = params.unpackFlipY;
1871 if (params.dstFlipX)
1872 {
1873 unpackFlipX = !unpackFlipX;
1874 }
1875 if (params.dstFlipY)
1876 {
1877 unpackFlipY = !unpackFlipY;
1878 }
1879 GetBlitTexCoords(srcWidth, srcHeight, params.srcRect, params.srcYFlipped, unpackFlipX,
1880 unpackFlipY, &u0, &v0, &u1, &v1);
1881
1882 BlitStencilToBufferParamsUniform uniform;
1883 uniform.srcTexCoordSteps[0] = (u1 - u0) / params.dstRect.width;
1884 uniform.srcTexCoordSteps[1] = (v1 - v0) / params.dstRect.height;
1885 uniform.srcStartTexCoords[0] = u0 + uniform.srcTexCoordSteps[0] * 0.5f;
1886 uniform.srcStartTexCoords[1] = v0 + uniform.srcTexCoordSteps[1] * 0.5f;
1887 uniform.srcLevel = params.srcLevel.get();
1888 uniform.srcLayer = params.srcLayer;
1889 uniform.dstSize[0] = params.dstRect.width;
1890 uniform.dstSize[1] = params.dstRect.height;
1891 uniform.dstBufferRowPitch = bufferRequiredRowPitch;
1892 uniform.resolveMS = params.dstStencil->samples() == 1;
1893
1894 cmdEncoder->setTexture(params.srcStencil, 1);
1895
1896 cmdEncoder->setData(uniform, 0);
1897 cmdEncoder->setBufferForWrite(mStencilCopyBuffer, 0, 1);
1898
1899 NSUInteger w = pipeline.threadExecutionWidth;
1900 MTLSize threadsPerThreadgroup = MTLSizeMake(w, 1, 1);
1901 DispatchCompute(contextMtl, cmdEncoder, /** allowNonUniform */ true,
1902 MTLSizeMake(params.dstRect.width, params.dstRect.height, 1),
1903 threadsPerThreadgroup);
1904
1905 // Copy buffer to real destination texture
1906 ASSERT(params.dstStencil->textureType() != MTLTextureType3D);
1907
1908 mtl::BlitCommandEncoder *blitEncoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
1909
1910 // Only copy the scissored area of the buffer.
1911 MTLScissorRect viewportRectMtl =
1912 GetScissorRect(params.dstRect, params.dstTextureSize.height, params.dstFlipY);
1913 MTLScissorRect scissorRectMtl =
1914 GetScissorRect(params.dstScissorRect, params.dstTextureSize.height, params.dstFlipY);
1915
1916 uint32_t dx = static_cast<uint32_t>(scissorRectMtl.x - viewportRectMtl.x);
1917 uint32_t dy = static_cast<uint32_t>(scissorRectMtl.y - viewportRectMtl.y);
1918
1919 uint32_t bufferStartReadableOffset = dx + bufferRequiredRowPitch * dy;
1920 blitEncoder->copyBufferToTexture(
1921 mStencilCopyBuffer, bufferStartReadableOffset, bufferRequiredRowPitch, 0,
1922 MTLSizeMake(scissorRectMtl.width, scissorRectMtl.height, 1), params.dstStencil,
1923 params.dstStencilLayer, params.dstStencilLevel,
1924 MTLOriginMake(scissorRectMtl.x, scissorRectMtl.y, 0),
1925 params.dstPackedDepthStencilFormat ? MTLBlitOptionStencilFromDepthStencil
1926 : MTLBlitOptionNone);
1927
1928 return angle::Result::Continue;
1929}

1942AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> IndexGeneratorUtils::getIndexConversionPipeline(
1943 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
1944 gl::DrawElementsType srcType,
1945 uint32_t srcOffset)
1946{
1947 size_t elementSize = gl::GetDrawElementsTypeSize(srcType);
1948 BOOL aligned = (srcOffset % elementSize) == 0;
1949 int srcTypeKey = static_cast<int>(srcType);
1950 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> &cache =
1951 mIndexConversionPipelineCaches[srcTypeKey][aligned ? 1 : 0];
1952
1953 if (!cache)
1954 {
1955 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1956 {
1957 auto funcConstants = [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1958
1959 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&aligned
1960 type:MTLDataTypeBool
1961 withName:SOURCE_BUFFER_ALIGNED_CONSTANT_NAME];
1962
1963 NSString *shaderName = nil;
1964 switch (srcType)
1965 {
1966 case gl::DrawElementsType::UnsignedByte:
1967 // No need for specialized shader
1968 funcConstants = nil;
1969 shaderName = @"convertIndexU8ToU16";
1970 break;
1971 case gl::DrawElementsType::UnsignedShort:
1972 shaderName = @"convertIndexU16";
1973 break;
1974 case gl::DrawElementsType::UnsignedInt:
1975 shaderName = @"convertIndexU32";
1976 break;
1977 default:
1978 UNREACHABLE();
1979 }
1980
1981 EnsureSpecializedComputePipelineInitialized(contextMtl->getDisplay(), shaderName,
1982 funcConstants, &cache);
1983 }
1984 }
1985
1986 return cache;
1987}
1988
1989AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>>
1990IndexGeneratorUtils::getIndicesFromElemArrayGeneratorPipeline(
1991 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
1992 gl::DrawElementsType srcType,
1993 uint32_t srcOffset,
1994 NSString *shaderName,
1995 IndexConversionPipelineArray *pipelineCacheArray)
1996{
1997 size_t elementSize = gl::GetDrawElementsTypeSize(srcType);
1998 BOOL aligned = (srcOffset % elementSize) == 0;
1999 int srcTypeKey = static_cast<int>(srcType);
2000
2001 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> &cache =
2002 (*pipelineCacheArray)[srcTypeKey][aligned ? 1 : 0];
2003
2004 if (!cache)
2005 {
2006 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
2007 {
2008 auto funcConstants = [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
2009
2010 bool isU8 = false;
2011 bool isU16 = false;
2012 bool isU32 = false;
2013
2014 switch (srcType)
2015 {
2016 case gl::DrawElementsType::UnsignedByte:
2017 isU8 = true;
2018 break;
2019 case gl::DrawElementsType::UnsignedShort:
2020 isU16 = true;
2021 break;
2022 case gl::DrawElementsType::UnsignedInt:
2023 isU32 = true;
2024 break;
2025 default:
2026 UNREACHABLE();
2027 }
2028
2029 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&aligned
2030 type:MTLDataTypeBool
2031 withName:SOURCE_BUFFER_ALIGNED_CONSTANT_NAME];
2032 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&isU8
2033 type:MTLDataTypeBool
2034 withName:SOURCE_IDX_IS_U8_CONSTANT_NAME];
2035 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&isU16
2036 type:MTLDataTypeBool
2037 withName:SOURCE_IDX_IS_U16_CONSTANT_NAME];
2038 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&isU32
2039 type:MTLDataTypeBool
2040 withName:SOURCE_IDX_IS_U32_CONSTANT_NAME];
2041
2042 EnsureSpecializedComputePipelineInitialized(contextMtl->getDisplay(), shaderName,
2043 funcConstants, &cache);
2044 }
2045 }
2046
2047 return cache;
2048}

2062angle::Result IndexGeneratorUtils::convertIndexBufferGPU(ContextMtl *contextMtl,

2118
2119angle::Result IndexGeneratorUtils::generateTriFanBufferFromElementsArray(
2120 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2121 const IndexGenerationParams &params,
2122 uint32_t *indicesGenerated)
2123{
2124 const gl::VertexArray *vertexArray = contextMtl->getState().getVertexArray();
2125 const gl::Buffer *elementBuffer = vertexArray->getElementArrayBuffer();
2126 if (elementBuffer)
2127 {
2128 BufferMtl *elementBufferMtl = GetImpl(elementBuffer);

2496 type:MTLDataTypeBool
2497 withName:VISIBILITY_RESULT_KEEP_OLD_VAL_CONSTANT_NAME];

2500 contextMtl->getDisplay(), @"combineVisibilityResult", funcConstants, &cache);

2503 return cache;

2506void VisibilityResultUtils::combineVisibilityResult(
2507 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2508 bool keepOldValue,
2509 const VisibilityBufferOffsetsMtl &renderPassResultBufOffsets,
2510 const BufferRef &renderPassResultBuf,
2511 const BufferRef &finalResultBuf)
2512{
2513 ASSERT(!renderPassResultBufOffsets.empty());
2514
2515 if (renderPassResultBufOffsets.size() == 1 && !keepOldValue)
2516 {
2517 // Use blit command to copy directly
2518 BlitCommandEncoder *blitEncoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
2519
2520 blitEncoder->copyBuffer(renderPassResultBuf, renderPassResultBufOffsets.front(),
2521 finalResultBuf, 0, kOcclusionQueryResultSize);
2522 return;
2523 }
2524
2525 ComputeCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder = contextMtl->getComputeCommandEncoder();
2526 ASSERT(cmdEncoder);
2527
2528 id<MTLComputePipelineState> pipeline =
2529 getVisibilityResultCombPipeline(contextMtl, keepOldValue);
2530 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(pipeline);
2531
2532 CombineVisibilityResultUniform options;
2533 // Offset is viewed as 64 bit unit in compute shader.
2534 options.startOffset = renderPassResultBufOffsets.front() / kOcclusionQueryResultSize;
2535 options.numOffsets = renderPassResultBufOffsets.size();
2536
2537 cmdEncoder->setData(options, 0);
2538 cmdEncoder->setBuffer(renderPassResultBuf, 0, 1);
2539 cmdEncoder->setBufferForWrite(finalResultBuf, 0, 2);
2540
2541 DispatchCompute(contextMtl, cmdEncoder, pipeline, 1);
2542}

2577angle::Result MipmapUtils::generateMipmapCS(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2578 const TextureRef &srcTexture,
2579 bool sRGBMipmap,
2580 NativeTexLevelArray * mipmapOutputViews)
2581{
2582 ComputeCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder = contextMtl->getComputeCommandEncoder();
2583 ASSERT(cmdEncoder);
2584
2585 MTLSize threadGroupSize;
2586 uint32_t slices = 1;
2587 switch (srcTexture->textureType())
2588 {
2589 case MTLTextureType2D:
2590 ensure2DMipGeneratorPipelineInitialized(contextMtl);
2591 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(m2DMipGeneratorPipeline);
2592 threadGroupSize = MTLSizeMake(kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim,
2593 kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim, 1);
2594 break;
2595 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
2596 ensure2DArrayMipGeneratorPipelineInitialized(contextMtl);
2597 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(m2DArrayMipGeneratorPipeline);
2598 slices = srcTexture->arrayLength();
2599 threadGroupSize = MTLSizeMake(kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim,
2600 kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim, 1);
2601 break;
2602 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
2603 ensureCubeMipGeneratorPipelineInitialized(contextMtl);
2604 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(mCubeMipGeneratorPipeline);
2605 slices = 6;
2606 threadGroupSize = MTLSizeMake(kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim,
2607 kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim, 1);
2608 break;
2609 case MTLTextureType3D:
2610 ensure3DMipGeneratorPipelineInitialized(contextMtl);
2611 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(m3DMipGeneratorPipeline);
2612 threadGroupSize =
2613 MTLSizeMake(kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim, kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim,
2614 kGenerateMipThreadGroupSizePerDim);
2615 break;
2616 default:
2617 UNREACHABLE();
2618 }
2619
2620 Generate3DMipmapUniform options;
2621 uint32_t maxMipsPerBatch = 4;
2622
2623 uint32_t remainMips = srcTexture->mipmapLevels() - 1;
2624 options.srcLevel = 0;
2625
2626 cmdEncoder->setTexture(srcTexture, 0);
2627 cmdEncoder->markResourceBeingWrittenByGPU(srcTexture);
2628 while (remainMips)
2629 {
2630 const TextureRef &firstMipView = mipmapOutputViews->at(mtl::MipmapNativeLevel(options.srcLevel + 1));
2631 gl::Extents size = firstMipView->sizeAt0();
2632 bool isPow2 = gl::isPow2(size.width) && gl::isPow2(size.height) && gl::isPow2(size.depth);
2633
2634 // Currently multiple mipmaps generation is only supported for power of two base level.
2635 if (isPow2)
2636 {
2637 options.numMipmapsToGenerate = std::min(remainMips, maxMipsPerBatch);
2638 }
2639 else
2640 {
2641 options.numMipmapsToGenerate = 1;
2642 }
2643
2644 cmdEncoder->setData(options, 0);
2645
2646 for (uint32_t i = 1; i <= options.numMipmapsToGenerate; ++i)
2647 {
2648 cmdEncoder->setTexture(mipmapOutputViews->at(mtl::MipmapNativeLevel(options.srcLevel + i)), i);
2649 }
2650
2651 uint32_t threadsPerZ = std::max(slices, firstMipView->depthAt0());
2652
2653 DispatchCompute(contextMtl, cmdEncoder,
2654 /** allowNonUniform */ false,
2655 MTLSizeMake(firstMipView->widthAt0(), firstMipView->heightAt0(), threadsPerZ),
2656 threadGroupSize);
2657
2658 remainMips -= options.numMipmapsToGenerate;
2659 options.srcLevel += options.numMipmapsToGenerate;
2660 }
2661
2662 return angle::Result::Continue;
2663}

2679AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> CopyPixelsUtils::getPixelsCopyPipeline(
2680 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2681 const angle::Format &angleFormat,
2682 const TextureRef &texture,
2683 bool bufferWrite)
2684{
2685 int formatIDValue = static_cast<int>(angleFormat.id);
2686 int shaderTextureType = GetShaderTextureType(texture);
2687 int index2 = mtl_shader::kTextureTypeCount * (bufferWrite ? 1 : 0) + shaderTextureType;
2688
2689 auto &cache = mPixelsCopyPipelineCaches[formatIDValue][index2];
2690
2691 if (!cache)
2692 {
2693 // Pipeline not cached, create it now:
2694 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
2695 {
2696 auto funcConstants = [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
2697
2698 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&formatIDValue
2699 type:MTLDataTypeInt
2700 withName:COPY_FORMAT_TYPE_CONSTANT_NAME];
2701 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&shaderTextureType
2702 type:MTLDataTypeInt
2703 withName:PIXEL_COPY_TEXTURE_TYPE_CONSTANT_NAME];
2704
2705 NSString *shaderName = nil;
2706 if (bufferWrite)
2707 {
2708 shaderName = [NSString stringWithUTF8String:mWriteShaderName.c_str()];
2709 }
2710 else
2711 {
2712 shaderName = [NSString stringWithUTF8String:mReadShaderName.c_str()];
2713 }
2714
2715 EnsureSpecializedComputePipelineInitialized(contextMtl->getDisplay(), shaderName,
2716 funcConstants, &cache);
2717 }
2718 }
2719
2720 return cache;
2721}

2723angle::Result CopyPixelsUtils::unpackPixelsFromBufferToTexture(
2724 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2725 const angle::Format &srcAngleFormat,
2726 const CopyPixelsFromBufferParams &params)
2727{
2728 ComputeCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder = contextMtl->getComputeCommandEncoder();
2729 ASSERT(cmdEncoder);
2730
2731 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> pipeline =
2732 getPixelsCopyPipeline(contextMtl, srcAngleFormat, params.texture, false);
2733
2734 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(pipeline);
2735 cmdEncoder->setBuffer(params.buffer, 0, 1);
2736 cmdEncoder->setTextureForWrite(params.texture, 0);
2737
2738 CopyPixelFromBufferUniforms options;
2739 options.copySize[0] = params.textureArea.width;
2740 options.copySize[1] = params.textureArea.height;
2741 options.copySize[2] = params.textureArea.depth;
2742 options.bufferStartOffset = params.bufferStartOffset;
2743 options.pixelSize = srcAngleFormat.pixelBytes;
2744 options.bufferRowPitch = params.bufferRowPitch;
2745 options.bufferDepthPitch = params.bufferDepthPitch;
2746 options.textureOffset[0] = params.textureArea.x;
2747 options.textureOffset[1] = params.textureArea.y;
2748 options.textureOffset[2] = params.textureArea.z;
2749 cmdEncoder->setData(options, 0);
2750
2751 NSUInteger w = pipeline.get().threadExecutionWidth;
2752 MTLSize threadsPerThreadgroup = MTLSizeMake(w, 1, 1);
2753
2754 MTLSize threads =
2755 MTLSizeMake(params.textureArea.width, params.textureArea.height, params.textureArea.depth);
2756
2757 DispatchCompute(contextMtl, cmdEncoder,
2758 /** allowNonUniform */ true, threads, threadsPerThreadgroup);

2760 return angle::Result::Continue;
2761}

2763angle::Result CopyPixelsUtils::packPixelsFromTextureToBuffer(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2764 const angle::Format &dstAngleFormat,
2765 const CopyPixelsToBufferParams &params)
2766{
2767 ComputeCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder = contextMtl->getComputeCommandEncoder();
2768 ASSERT(cmdEncoder);
2769
2770 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> pipeline =
2771 getPixelsCopyPipeline(contextMtl, dstAngleFormat, params.texture, true);
2772
2773 cmdEncoder->setComputePipelineState(pipeline);
2774 cmdEncoder->setTexture(params.texture, 0);
2775 cmdEncoder->setBufferForWrite(params.buffer, 0, 1);
2776
2777 WritePixelToBufferUniforms options;
2778 options.copySize[0] = params.textureArea.width;
2779 options.copySize[1] = params.textureArea.height;
2780 options.bufferStartOffset = params.bufferStartOffset;
2781 options.pixelSize = dstAngleFormat.pixelBytes;
2782 options.bufferRowPitch = params.bufferRowPitch;
2783 options.textureOffset[0] = params.textureArea.x;
2784 options.textureOffset[1] = params.textureArea.y;
2785 options.textureLevel = params.textureLevel.get();
2786 options.textureLayer = params.textureSliceOrDeph;
2787 options.reverseTextureRowOrder = params.reverseTextureRowOrder;
2788 cmdEncoder->setData(options, 0);
2789
2790 NSUInteger w = pipeline.get().threadExecutionWidth;
2791 MTLSize threadsPerThreadgroup = MTLSizeMake(w, 1, 1);
2792
2793 MTLSize threads = MTLSizeMake(params.textureArea.width, params.textureArea.height, 1);
2794
2795 DispatchCompute(contextMtl, cmdEncoder,
2796 /** allowNonUniform */ true, threads, threadsPerThreadgroup);
2797
2798 return angle::Result::Continue;
2799}

2990AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>>
2991VertexFormatConversionUtils::getFloatConverstionComputePipeline(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
2992 const angle::Format &srcAngleFormat)
2993{
2994 int formatIDValue = static_cast<int>(srcAngleFormat.id);
2995
2996 auto &cache = mConvertToFloatCompPipelineCaches[formatIDValue];
2997
2998 if (!cache)
2999 {
3000 // Pipeline not cached, create it now:
3001 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
3002 {
3003 auto funcConstants = [[[MTLFunctionConstantValues alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
3004
3005 [funcConstants setConstantValue:&formatIDValue
3006 type:MTLDataTypeInt
3007 withName:COPY_FORMAT_TYPE_CONSTANT_NAME];
3008
3009 EnsureSpecializedComputePipelineInitialized(
3010 contextMtl->getDisplay(), @"convertToFloatVertexFormatCS", funcConstants, &cache);
3011 }
3012 }
3013
3014 return cache;
3015}

3047AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLLibrary>> TransformFeedbackUtils::createMslXfbLibrary(
3048 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
3049 const std::string &translatedMsl)
3050{
3051 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
3052 {
3053 DisplayMtl *display = contextMtl->getDisplay();
3054 id<MTLDevice> mtlDevice = display->getMetalDevice();
3055
3056 // Convert to actual binary shader
3057 mtl::AutoObjCPtr<NSError *> err = nil;
3058 mtl::AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLLibrary>> mtlShaderLib =
3059 mtl::CreateShaderLibrary(mtlDevice, translatedMsl, @{@"TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_ENABLED": @"1"}, &err);
3060 if (err && !mtlShaderLib)
3061 {
3062 NSLog(@"%@", err.get());
3063 assert(0);
3064 }
3065 mtlShaderLib.get().label = @"TransformFeedback";
3066 return mtlShaderLib;
3067 }

3070AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLRenderPipelineState>> TransformFeedbackUtils::getTransformFeedbackRenderPipeline(
3071 ContextMtl *contextMtl,
3072 RenderCommandEncoder *cmdEncoder,
3073 mtl::RenderPipelineDesc &pipelineDesc)
3074{
3075 const ProgramMtl *programMtl = mtl::GetImpl(contextMtl->getState().getProgram());
3076 RenderPipelineCache &cache = *programMtl->mMetalXfbRenderPipelineCache;
3077
3078 if (!cache.getVertexShader())
3079 {
3080 // Pipeline cache not intialized, do it now:
3081 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
3082 {
3083 auto shaderLib = createMslXfbLibrary(contextMtl, programMtl->getTranslatedShaderSource(gl::ShaderType::Vertex));
3084 // Non specialized constants provided, use default creation function.
3085 EnsureVertexShaderOnlyPipelineCacheInitialized(contextMtl, SHADER_ENTRY_NAME, shaderLib,
3086 &cache);
3087 }
3088 }
3089
3090 RenderPipelineDesc xfbPipelineDesc =
3091 GetTransformFeedbackRenderPipelineDesc(cmdEncoder, pipelineDesc);
3092
3093 return cache.getRenderPipelineState(contextMtl, xfbPipelineDesc);
3094}
